  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\n(based on this incident: https://notes.status.im/5apzxihzQcqRN0WzpvL6SQ)\r\n\r\nCurrently, we have a constant timeout for receiving messages from mailserver. If a message we think as \"last\" fails to come, we re-request everything again. If the mailserver is too slow, these re-tries can cause cascading effects.\r\n\r\nA few possible improvements to this algorithm are:\r\n- increase timeout time with every failure;\r\n- limit timeouts for 2 times per mailserver, if still no answer, try switching to another one. If all are exausted â€” show an error.\r\n- (maybe) request a shorter time span\r\n- ???\r\n\r\n# Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nWe don't re-request data from the same mailserver over and over again if it fails.\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://notes.status.im/5apzxihzQcqRN0WzpvL6SQ\">[FIXED] Suspicious mailserver traffic spike - CodiMD</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
